Patch Set 2:

Three comments on optimization are addressed for CPININFO, MEAS and CSQ commands as per the review comments. Patch is merged and ready for code review.

Below are the list of comments and feedback from developer.
fwMODEM_Sim_Altair_Cpininfo:
1.         Code can be written without using the 4 local variables. Use the code <3-clModem_sim.pin.pin_counter> directly in the sprint().
                        sprintf(string,"\r\n+CPININFO: %d,%d,%d,%d\r\n",3-clModem_sim.pin.pin_counter, repeat for others. 
2.         Suggestion Avoid hardcoding – Code will be readable.
Developer Feedback: Local variables are required, otherwise the sprintf instruction will be lengthier.
Legacy code has the max retry count to 3 and 10 without macro. I will introduce macro for these count. Legacy code will also have minimal change.

fwMODEM_Sim_Altair_Ccid:
1.         Line 1965: what is the correction factor 2, why is it required. Either add a comment or define a macro with meaningful name. 
2.         sim_out.len is already 19 or 20 bytes. Again why scale by a factor of 2.
Developer Feedback: There will be 2 bytes are status word, which should be subtracted from the output data. Since it is the way, sim output is parsed, comment is not included. 
3.         Temp_buf usage can be avoided. Directly use pointers to msg[]. Can avoid memcpy also.
Developer Feedback: temp_buf[] will have the hex to ascii converted data. We need this conversion before we pack the response.

fwMODEM_Cfg_Altair_Setcfg:
1.         Repetative code for most of the params, looks like hard coding. Suggestion is to maintain a table , which will be populated in the beginning. Write some generic piece of code which can handle the request by reading the contents of table.
Developer Feedback: This command can come with maximum 16 parameters p[0] to p[15]. Also there are 83 possible options for p[0]. We felt table would not be helping and hence the same is not used for implementation.

fwMODEM_Cfg_Altair_Getcfg:
1.Please check if a table can be used and indexed to access the required field. This will avoid too many “if” “else”
Developer Feedback:This command can come with maximum of 2 parameters. There are 85 possible options for p[0]. Since it is not the straight forward access for many parameters, we have not used the table.

fwMODEM_Cfg_Altair_GetOtpcmd:
1.         fwMODEM_SndData can be called only once in the end after the string is populated, instead of calling it in multiple places.
Developer Feedback: In the implementation, there are always success and failure legs. In the success case, we will send only the final response. In the failure case, we will send ERROR string. Once we come out of the "WR" mode, we will not know whether we have come out from success leg or failure leg. Either we have to respond to sut from the respective leg, or we should put a flag to say it is success or failure. Hence we have chosen the first option.

fwMODEM_Cfg_Altair_Ver
1.Function header can be more descriptive
2.Code can be changed to have just  one call to fwMODEM_SndData. fwMODEM_SndData with same parameters called in multiple places.
Developer Feedback: This command handler is almost 90% not matching with Specification. It is implemented as per CFO's test results. It is very strange that the response is same for read, test and action command with ALL, GPS and WIFI option. But we coded as per CFO’s test results. Handler will be updated once we get the actual response from client.

fwMODEM_Cfg_Altair_Status

2. There has to be some logic which determines the state of the modem. No clarity on the hard coded values.
Developer Feedback: The default status for all the components are not mentioned in the document. It has been informed to client about the defaults status. This handler will be updated if we receive any default status. If not, user has to set the status as per their use case.

Developer Feedback: As per CFO's response, we have maintained only one cell in the implementation. It can be updated in the future. We are using this variable in the "for" loop to send the cell details. We are not seeing any limit check. Please confirm whether I am missing anything.

fwMODEM_Telecom_Altair_Meas:

Developer Feedback: It is just a simulation and hence we are not starting any RF test. Hence "Rx and Tx test abort" will be responded with just "OK"

fwMODEM_GPRS_MAX_SUP_CID has max value of 5 as defined in header file, fwModem_gprs.h . So we are checking the condition here. In handler code we have taken care to check cid >= fwMODEM_GPRS_MAX_SUP_CID and then provides error response if it exceeds max range for cid value. Check once fwMODEM_GPRS_MAX_SUP_CID has max value of 5 as defined in header file. Hence cid used without any range check.This is only a temporary buffer and we are not allocating any memory here. It should start at the beginning of the line only, which is the coding standard being followed.Based on the first character of sca parameter,then value is set to 145, else default is 129, as per AT spec doc. strP0Cntr is incremented, else might end up with inappropriate response.
